You can define environment variable [dynamically][1], e.g.:

```
pipeline {
    agent any
    environment {
        GIT_MESSAGE = &quot;&quot;&quot;${sh(
            script: &#39;git log --no-walk --format=format:%s ${GIT_COMMIT}&#39;, 
            returnStdout: true
            )}&quot;&quot;&quot;
    }
    stages {
        stage(&#39;test&#39;) {
            steps {
                sh &#39;echo &quot;Message: --${GIT_MESSAGE}--&quot;&#39;
            }
        }
    }
}
```

[1]: https://jenkins.io/doc/book/pipeline/jenkinsfile/#setting-environment-variables-dynamically

